    "description": {
      "value": "<p><b>Source</b> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 20</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 134</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><b>Cost</b> 2 gp <b>Weight</b> -</p><p><b>Damage</b> 1d2 (small), 1d3 (medium); <b>Critical</b> x2; <b>Range</b> -; <b>Type</b> P; <b>Special</b> disarm, see text</p><p><b>Category</b> Light; <b>Proficiency</b> Exotic</p><p><b>Weapon Groups</b> Close</p><h3>Description</h3><p>Also known as an iron claw, this device consists of a fanlike structure of three or more 10-inch blades secured to a sturdy handle strapped to the forearm of the off hand. It can be used as an offensive weapon or defensively like a buckler, or used to disarm an opponent without provoking an attack of opportunity. It provides its owner with a +2 circumstance bonus on attempts to disarm or sunder swords or other slender-bladed weapons.</p>"
